68// Native modules cached by their wire bytes and compile-time imports.
69class NativeModuleCache {
70 public:
71 struct Key {
72 // Store the prefix hash as part of the key for faster lookup, and to
73 // quickly check existing prefixes for streaming compilation.
74 size_t prefix_hash;
75 CompileTimeImports compile_imports;
76 base::Vector<const uint8_t> bytes;
77
78 bool operator==(const Key& other) const {
79 bool eq =
80 bytes == other.bytes && compile_imports == other.compile_imports;
81 DCHECK_IMPLIES(eq, prefix_hash == other.prefix_hash);
82 return eq;
83 }
84
85 bool operator<(const Key& other) const {
86 if (prefix_hash != other.prefix_hash) {
87 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!bytes.empty() && !other.bytes.empty(),
88 bytes != other.bytes);
89 return prefix_hash < other.prefix_hash;
90 }
91 if (compile_imports != other.compile_imports) {
92 return compile_imports.ToIntegral() <
93 other.compile_imports.ToIntegral();
94 }
95 if (bytes.size() != other.bytes.size()) {
96 return bytes.size() < other.bytes.size();
97 }
98 // Fast path when the base pointers are the same.
99 // Also handles the {nullptr} case which would be UB for memcmp.
100 if (bytes.begin() == other.bytes.begin()) {
101 DCHECK_EQ(prefix_hash, other.prefix_hash);
102 return false;
103 }
104 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(bytes.begin());
105 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(other.bytes.begin());
106 return memcmp(bytes.begin(), other.bytes.begin(), bytes.size()) < 0;
107 }
108 };
109
110 std::shared_ptr<NativeModule> MaybeGetNativeModule(
111 ModuleOrigin origin, base::Vector<const uint8_t> wire_bytes,
112 CompileTimeImports compile_imports);
113 bool GetStreamingCompilationOwnership(size_t prefix_hash,
114 CompileTimeImports compile_imports);
115 void StreamingCompilationFailed(size_t prefix_hash,
116 CompileTimeImports compile_imports);
117 std::shared_ptr<NativeModule> Update(
118 std::shared_ptr<NativeModule> native_module, bool error);
119 void Erase(NativeModule* native_module);
120
121 bool empty() { return map_.empty(); }
122
123 // Hash the wire bytes up to the code section header. Used as a heuristic to
124 // avoid streaming compilation of modules that are likely already in the
125 // cache. See {GetStreamingCompilationOwnership}. Assumes that the bytes have
126 // already been validated.
127 static size_t PrefixHash(base::Vector<const uint8_t> wire_bytes);
128
129 private:
130 // Each key points to the corresponding native module's wire bytes, so they
131 // should always be valid as long as the native module is alive. When
132 // the native module dies, {FreeNativeModule} deletes the entry from the
133 // map, so that we do not leave any dangling key pointing to an expired
134 // weak_ptr. This also serves as a way to regularly clean up the map, which
135 // would otherwise accumulate expired entries.
136 // A {nullopt} value is inserted to indicate that this native module is
137 // currently being created in some thread, and that other threads should wait
138 // before trying to get it from the cache.
139 // By contrast, an expired {weak_ptr} indicates that the native module died
140 // and will soon be cleaned up from the cache.
141 std::map<Key, base::Optional<std::weak_ptr<NativeModule>>> map_;
142
143 base::Mutex mutex_;
144
145 // This condition variable is used to synchronize threads compiling the same
146 // module. Only one thread will create the {NativeModule}. Other threads
147 // will wait on this variable until the first thread wakes them up.
148 base::ConditionVariable cache_cv_;
149};

296 // Create a new NativeModule. The caller is responsible for its
297 // lifetime. The native module will be given some memory for code,
298 // which will be page size aligned. The size of the initial memory
299 // is determined by {code_size_estimate}. The native module may later request
300 // more memory.
301 // TODO(wasm): isolate is only required here for CompilationState.
302 std::shared_ptr<NativeModule> NewNativeModule(
303 Isolate* isolate, WasmFeatures enabled_features,
304 CompileTimeImports compile_imports,
305 std::shared_ptr<const WasmModule> module, size_t code_size_estimate);
306
307 // Try getting a cached {NativeModule}, or get ownership for its creation.
308 // Return {nullptr} if no {NativeModule} exists for these bytes. In this case,
309 // a {nullopt} entry is added to let other threads know that a {NativeModule}
310 // for these bytes is currently being created. The caller should eventually
311 // call {UpdateNativeModuleCache} to update the entry and wake up other
312 // threads. The {wire_bytes}' underlying array should be valid at least until
313 // the call to {UpdateNativeModuleCache}.
314 // The provided {CompileTimeImports} are considered part of the caching key,
315 // because they change the generated code as well as the behavior of the
316 // {imports()} function of any WasmModuleObjects we'll create for this
317 // NativeModule later.
318 std::shared_ptr<NativeModule> MaybeGetNativeModule(
319 ModuleOrigin origin, base::Vector<const uint8_t> wire_bytes,
320 CompileTimeImports compile_imports, Isolate* isolate);
321
322 // Replace the temporary {nullopt} with the new native module, or
323 // erase it if any error occurred. Wake up blocked threads waiting for this
324 // module.
325 // To avoid a deadlock on the main thread between synchronous and streaming
326 // compilation, two compilation jobs might compile the same native module at
327 // the same time. In this case the first call to {UpdateNativeModuleCache}
328 // will insert the native module in the cache, and the last call will receive
329 // the existing entry from the cache.
330 // Return the cached entry, or {native_module} if there was no previously
331 // cached module.
332 std::shared_ptr<NativeModule> UpdateNativeModuleCache(
333 bool has_error, std::shared_ptr<NativeModule> native_module,
334 Isolate* isolate);
335
336 // Register this prefix hash for a streaming compilation job.
337 // If the hash is not in the cache yet, the function returns true and the
338 // caller owns the compilation of this module.
339 // Otherwise another compilation job is currently preparing or has already
340 // prepared a module with the same prefix hash. The caller should wait until
341 // the stream is finished and call {MaybeGetNativeModule} to either get the
342 // module from the cache or get ownership for the compilation of these bytes.
343 bool GetStreamingCompilationOwnership(size_t prefix_hash,
344 CompileTimeImports compile_imports);
345
346 // Remove the prefix hash from the cache when compilation failed. If
347 // compilation succeeded, {UpdateNativeModuleCache} should be called instead.
348 void StreamingCompilationFailed(size_t prefix_hash,
349 CompileTimeImports compile_imports);
350
351 void FreeNativeModule(NativeModule*);
352 void ClearWeakScriptHandle(Isolate* isolate,

355 // Sample the code size of the given {NativeModule} in all isolates that have

358 void SampleTopTierCodeSizeInAllIsolates(const std::shared_ptr<NativeModule>&);

360 // Called by each Isolate to report its live code for a GC cycle. First

362 // second version gets live code from the execution stack of that isolate.
363 void ReportLiveCodeForGC(Isolate*, base::Vector<WasmCode*>);
364 void ReportLiveCodeFromStackForGC(Isolate*);
365
366 // Add potentially dead code. The occurrence in the set of potentially dead
367 // code counts as a reference, and is decremented on the next GC.
368 // Returns {true} if the code was added to the set of potentially dead code,
369 // {false} if an entry already exists. The ref count is *unchanged* in any
370 // case.
371 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT bool AddPotentiallyDeadCode(WasmCode*);
